Commit Message: Initial import of files.

Forget to commit the file in a previous commit.

Update of ignoring files.

Merge local.py and remote.py into one file.
Add gitignore file.
Rewrite and clean copy methods for both LocaHost and RemoteHost.
Add exception for invalid os in 'systems' plugin
Replace hostname attribut by a property.
Export plugins to individual repositories.
Rename the method for printing the status of a command and add a parameter for exiting the program if the command has failed.
Replace some OSError raise by classic list return.
Transform 'get_os' and 'get_arch' methods of the RemoteHost class to properties.
Change type (tuple -> list) of returns of executions functions

Correct a bug when checking 'directory' type + correct the exception
raised when list files of a file.

Update status functions for printing instead of returning + add
an exeception that is raised when 'quit' is passed to True in
'fail' and 'status' functions
Update the thread for printing the progress when copying from a remote host to an other host
Correct a bug in shell table printing

Rewritting the package for managing both localhost and remotes
hosts in the same way. Add a sub package for managing Linux hosts.
Rename README file for github.
Fix a bug in setup file due to the renaming of README file.

Uniformize 'stdout' and 'stderr' string and correct a bug in listdir
function.
Correct some incorrect variables names.
Fix a bad parenthesis.

Remove a check in 'read' method of the 'Remote' object. This check was
checking if the 'path' parameter was a file but it introduce a bug with
Linux chroot. Indeed, 'read' function in 'Linux' object, call the parent
function via the 'super' keywork and the check don't check the path in
the chroot filesystem but in the parent filesystem (call the parent
'isfile' function)! Any function in 'Remote' object called via 'super'
keyword in 'Linux' object should not call internal function of the
object.
Improve 'size' function.
Correct some errors in linux subpackage.
Improve network configuration of Deb based hosts by creating one file per interfaces.
Updating Rpm based object with functions for setting hostname and network configuration.
Add some properties in Deb object for retrieving OS version.
Update generation of network configuration for hosts based on debian (one file per interface for Ubuntu>11.04).
Add unix/utils.py file which contain (for now) method for converting sizes.
Set license (MIT).
Update of the setup.
Change format for README (markdown -> reStructuredText).
Update setup.py file.
Conversion methods in 'utils' module now return int or float according to 'toint' parameter.
Correct command for getting architecture.
Add which method for retrieving path of a command.
Add Pypi classifiers.
Add a property in Linux class for retrieving distribution (based on lsb_release).
Prepare rewrite of the package.

Add the 'host' module that defining 'Local' and 'Remote' classes inheriting from
the abstract class 'Host'. For the 'Remote' object, the method for connecting to
a remote host has been implemented. Both classes also have an 'execute' method
for executing commands.

Implements some common commands. Some of the commands has been implements
through intermediaries objects.
Add SSH agent forwarding.
Correct some bugs in get method.
unix:host: Move '_Path' object at the end of the file.

* Replace '__ip' private attribute of 'Remote' class by a public attribute.
* Use weekref objects attach to a host (like _Path).

Add a _Remote object attach to a Host allowing to copy files from the current
host to a remote host using differents methods ('scp', 'tar', ...). SCP method
has been implemented.
unix:host: Add a 'rsync' method to '_Remote' object.

* Move 'format_command' method at the module level.
* Options with a dash in there are passed to the 'format_command' with an
  underscore because python not allowed dash in arguments names.
Move everything in 'host' module at the package level (unix/__init__.py).

unix: Add a logger (configuration of formatter and handlers must be done in
the main program).
unix: Use properties when using attached object (like Path, Users, ...).
Add a 'shell' module for shell printing.

shell: Improve 'table_line' function (multiples lines for column value that
contain newline or len bigger than size.)

unix: Add an attribut 'options_behaviour' to 'Host' class allowing to define if
options must be put before or after arguments (default: before) when executing a
command. There's also a context manager for this behviour.
unix: Add a context manager for connecting to a remote a host.
unix: Add a class for managing users.
unix: Add a class for managing groups.
unix: Add a class for managing processes.
unix: Add methods for mount/umount commands.
unix: force conversion of all command arguments to string.
unix: Use pythonic version of execute for uname fonctions.
unix: Some coding style changes.
unix: Use six.iteritems() for python 2/3 compatibility.
unix: Add some strings compatibilty between python 2/3.
Add python 2/3 compatibility for 'range' and unicode strings.
unix:shell: Correct encoding error.
shell: Improve column split algorithm and add colorizing values.

unix: stdout and stderr are not split anymore because theses results in Python3
are bytes string which must be decoded.
Add a method for opening files.
shell: Correct a bug when printing a table line.

Add controls for controlling some behaviours like decoding, locale and options
place.
Remove some functions and exceptions.
Improve connection check in Remote class.
unix: Clean 'connect' method of 'Remote' object.

unix:
  * Clean code in _Remote class.
  * Correct a bug when copying from a remote to localhost and not being
    connecting as root to the remote host.
shell: Add functions for flushing and pretty printing messages.
sizes: Add a module for converting sizes.
Correct a bug for python3.
unix: Correct a bug when executing a remote command with non string parameters.
unix: Add a tail method on both Local and Remote objects allowing to tail -f.

unix: Correct a bug with stderr (which was not decoded) when excuted an
      interactive command on a remote host.
unix: Change the error message when there is no connection to a remote host.

unix:
    * Add a method 'is_connected' to the 'Local' object for compatibility with
      the 'Remote' object. The method always return True.
    * '_conn' attribute, which contains the 'SSHClient' object, is now
       initialized in the constuctor. The method 'is_connected' does not check
       anymore for the presence of attribute in the object but if the value of
       the attribute is None.

unix:
    * Update the 'instances' function: it now return the list of the
      inheritances from the higher object, but ignoring 'object' and 'Host'
      types (ie: the first element is 'Local' or 'Remote'). For the remaining
      types, the string 'Host' is removed (ie: 'LinuxHost' becomes 'Linux').
    * Add a method 'isvalid' that raise an exception if the first type in the
      inheritance chain is not 'Local' or 'Remote'.

unix: Add a static method 'clone' to 'Local' and 'Remote' objects allowing to
      clone the object. It takes an instance at parameter and return a new
      instance of the same type but with attributes of the given instance.

unix: Update the 'which' method of the 'Host' object for raising an exception
      if the command is not found.

unix: Update the 'size' method of the 'Host' object. Some default options
      have been added to the 'du' command and it now return an int.

unix: Add the methods 'mount' and 'umount' to the 'Host' object for
      mounting/unmounting partitions.
Update gitignore file for ignoring virtualenvs.
unix:linux: Create a package for managing Linux hosts.
unix:linux: Add functions for retrieving the distribution of a linux host.

unix:linux: Add chroot capability (with a context manager that detect the
            distribution and mount special devices).

unix:linux: Add an object for managing modules. It is accessible from the
             'modules' property of the 'LinuxHost' object.

unix:linux: Add a 'fstab' method to the 'LinuxHost' object allowing to parse
            the 'fstab' file for returning defined partitions.
unix:linux:distrib:arch: Add a module for managing Archlinux hosts.
unix:linux:distrib:debian: Add a module for managing Debian hosts.
unix:linux:distrib:ubuntu: Add a module for managing Ubuntu hosts.
unix:linux:distrib:redhat: Add a module for managing RedHat hosts.
unix:linux:distrib:centos: Add a module for managing CentOS hosts.

unix:linux: Add a context manager that connect to a remote host and return an
            instance of the detected distribution (or a 'LinuxHost' instance if
            the distribution can not be detected).
unix: Update some imports for linux subpackage.
Release version 0.1 with initial version before merging 'rewrite' branch.
unix: Set constants of the module as private.
unix:linux:distrib->unix:linux:gnu: Rename 'distrib' module to 'gnu'.
unix: Move properties objects to dedicated files.
unix:linux: Move properties objects to dedicated files.

unix:*: Remove invisible utf-8 characters in comments that generate errors with
        python 2.7.
unix:*: Some changes for having a compatibility with python2.7 and python3.3+.

unix: Some constants were not moved to properties' files. Imports for properties
      are now privates for preventing name's conflicts.

unix:linux: Imports for properties are now privates for preventing name's
            conflicts.

unix:linux: Update 'return_code' in 'LinuxHost' instance from the result of

unix: Force binary mode when opening a file for both 'Local' and 'Remote'

unix:linux: Correct 'distribution' method because of changes when opening files.

unix:linux: Add a 'Chroot' object for linux hosts for chroot instead of

unix:linux: Add a 'conf' properties allowing to set some configuration. For
            now, methods for setting passwords, generating SSH keys and setting
            'hosts' file have been implemented.
unix:linux: Some typos updates.

unix:linux:_conf: Correct a bug in 'set_password' method (shadow file was opened
in 'append' mode rather than 'write' mode).
unix:linux:gnu:*: Add getter and setter for managing hostname.

unix:linux:gnu:debian: Add a property 'network' with functions for managing
                       network. An unique has been created for generating the
                       configuration of '/etc/network/interfaces' and
                       '/etc/network/interfaces.d' files.

unix: Add a parameter 'STDIN' to the function 'execute' for allowing stdin
      redirects. For differentiating 'unix' parameters from the command's
      parameters, interactive parameter is now in uppercase (as stdin).
unix:linux:gnu:*: Correct a bug when parent is a chrooted host.
unix:shell: Add functions for getting width and height of the terminal.
unix:shell: Improve tables generation.
unix:linux: Add a property that retrieve memory informations in '/proc/meminfo'.
unix: Add some environment variables for locales when executing a command.
unix: Add a function for escaping spaces in paths.

unix:linux: Add a function for executing 'stat' on a file. It returns a '_Stat'
object whose properties execute the 'stat' command with a specific format.

unix: Method 'format_command' now returns a string rather than a list. This
      prevent to stringify the command in each command's call.

unix: Add the control 'shell' that force the execution with a specific shell. If

unix: Add an ugly hack that force the use of bash for Solaris systems as some
      commands (like 'test') differs with the default shell.

unix: Move the function for escaping paths to '_path' module and add some calls
      to this function.

unix: Add the function 'list' which is a wrapper to 'ls' command and simply
      'listdir' function by using it.

unix:_path: Add the function 'permissions' for retrieving permissions a file
            from the 'ls' command.

unix:_path: Add the function 'username' for retrieving the owner of a file from
            the 'ls' command.

unix:_path: Add the function 'groupname' for retrieving the group of a file from
            the 'ls' command.

unix:shell: Correct a bug in the 'table_line' function when a word in a column
is bigger than the column size.
Add a control for managing timeout on command execution.

Add the parameter 'keepalive' on 'connect' method (of 'Remote' object) for
keeping connection alive (http://paramiko-docs.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api/transport.html#paramiko.transport.Transport.set_keepalive).
Add a control for executing commands with custom environment variables.
users: Disable 'root' checks.
Update README and set version 1.0.
unix:linux: Correct a bug which cause /dev to be incorrectly mounted when chrooting.
unix: Add a control for executing a command with 'su'.
unix: Add methods for reading and writing a file completely.
unix: Add a method for replacing a pattern in a file.
unix: Add a context manager for mounting/unmounting a filesystem.
Coding style improvments.
unix:sizes: Add a method for pretty printing a value.
unix:shell: Correct a bug when printing a table line.
unix:linux: Add a property for managing fstab file.
unix:linux:_stat: Correct a call to in invalid function.
unix:linux: Add a property for managing kernel parameters (sysctl).
unix:linux: Add classes for managing services (Initd, Upstart and Systemd).
unix:linux:gnu:debian: Add a property for managing packages.

unix:linux:gnu:debian: When generating network configuration, sort additionals
parameters.
Rename modules.
unix:shell: Correct a bug when print tables with colors.

unix:linux:memory: Correct a bug with the regular expression raising an error
on some systems at the import.
unix: Use 'shlex' module for escaping arguments.

unix: Improve management of different shells.

Unix systems use various shells by default (Solaris use 'sh', FreeBSD use 'csh',
most Linux use 'bash'). Theses shells have differents behaviours ('test -e' is
replaced by 'test -r' for 'sh' in Solaris, 'csh' use the 'env' keyword for
managing environments variables, ...)!
'default_shell' attribute is set to the default shell (using 'echo $0' command)
and it is yet possible to use 'shell' control for executing a command with a
specific shell. It also manages environment variables according to the shell.
unix: Improve debug by adding a stream handler to the logger.
unix: Remove invisible utf8 characters which raised errors with python2.7.
unix: Add the detection of the default shell in the *Local* object.

unix: Correct a bug with python2.7.

In python2.7, 'quote' function is not in the 'shlex' module but in 'pipes'
module. So check the python version and import the function from right module.
unix: Add the control 'escape_args' for managing whether to escape arguments.

unix: Correct a bug with the default shell.

In "child" objects (ie: Linux, BSD, ...), the 'default_shell' attribute was not
set, which raised errors. The 'clone' method of 'Local' and 'Remote' objects
has been corrected for cloning this attribute.

unix: Add a 'STDOUT' options when executing commmands.

This option allows to redirect the output of a command to a file.
unix: Ignore options which have a null value.

unix: Update 'connect' context manager for managing localhost.

If hostname is 'localhost' the context manager returns a 'Local' object.
There is a new parameter 'force_ssh' for forcing a SSH connection to localhost
if wished.

unix:linux: Improve 'connect' context manager.

The context manager now inherit from the 'unix.connect' context manager.

Correct a bug whne cloning a 'Remote'.

The 'clone' method of 'Local' and 'Remote' objects allows to clone the
object and enforcing all attributes are copied in the resulted object.

For the 'Remote' object, the 'ip' attribute was not copied and thus
preventing some functions (like functions for remotely copying files)
to work.
Correct a bug preventing 'linux.connect' context manager to work with python 2.7.

Split execution of interactive command to its own methods.

The execution of interactive commands is now defined in the
'interactive' method (for both 'Local' and 'Remote' objects) instead of
using the special 'INTERACTIVE' option of the 'execute' method.

Two context managers '_get_chan' and '_forward_agent' have also be
defined for:
    * closing the agent forwarder and the channel after the execution of
      a command,
    * having reusable and more readable code between methods that
      execute commands

Improve management of outputs encoding.

The encoding of outputs is defined by the '_decode' attribute (its default value
is 'utf-8'). If the attribute is defined, outputs (stdout and stderr) will be of
type 'unicode' for python2 and 'str' for python3 with the given value of the
attribute used for decoding. If '_decode' value is None, python2 str/python3
bytes are returned.

'_decode' value can be set with the 'set_control' method of the 'set_controls'
context manager.

Add a method for itering over stdout and stderr (by returning a generator).

The 'iter' method has been defined for both 'Local' and 'Remote' and implements
a generator for itering over stdout and stderr lines. Each iteration is a tuple
of two elements with the firsh element indicating whether the line comes from
stdout and stderr and the second element the line value. The last tuple contains
the status of the command.

Correct a bug that make the 'iter' function of the 'Local' object slow.

Remove useless time.sleep(0.1) in the generator that was really slowing
the function.

Manage option used mutliple time in a command.

Some commands take the same option multiple times (like 'ldapsearch -LLL'
or 'ssh -vvv'). A list of value must be used in this case. If the value in
the list is a boolean, the option is added without value.

Add management of shell redirections.

Specials 'STDOUT' and 'STDERR' parameters of a command allows to define both
standard (>) and error (2>) redirection. If the value begin by a '+', the
append mode (>> or 2>>) is used.

Improve 'listdir' method.

'-1' option of the 'ls' command is forced for being sure to have one
file per line. The 'hidden' parameter has also been added for allowing
to return hidden files (excluding '.' and '..').

Update exceptions raised when listing directories.

Listing directories now raise IOError if the path not exists and OSError
for another errors.
